# Lockstep clang-tidy config — a BUG-FINDING gate, not a style gate.
#
# Rationale (learned by actually running it on Linux via tools/docker — the
# Apple toolchain can't run clang-tidy, so the prior config was authored blind):
# the prior config enabled every family (modernize/readability/misc) as ERRORS
# with FunctionCase=camelBack, while the codebase is consistently snake_case and
# uses printf in tooling/tests. Result: the gate failed on COSMETICS
# (printf-vs-std::println, snake_case names, could-be-const) — coverage theater
# that flags zero bugs. clang-tidy's real value is the static analyzer + the
# bug-pattern checks; cosmetic consistency is .clang-format's job, not a merge
# blocker.
#
# Enabled and treated as ERRORS — the families that catch correctness defects:
#   clang-analyzer-* : the static analyzer (use-after-free, null deref, leaks).
#   bugprone-*       : real bug patterns.
#   concurrency-*    : threading mistakes (cardinal rule 7).
#   performance-*    : cheap, behavior-preserving wins.
#   a few cppcoreguidelines SAFETY checks (RAII / ownership / member-init,
#   rules 6/7) — NOT the pedantic style ones.
# Disabled: high-noise subchecks that fire on deliberate systems-code choices
# (swappable params, narrowing in numeric code) and bury the signal.
#   - reinterpret-cast is NOT enabled: it is legitimate + necessary for the
#     byte/wire codecs (SimDisk, Raft message encoding), not a bug.
#   - concurrency-mt-unsafe is DISABLED: it flags getenv()/rand() as "not
#     thread safe", but the whole system is single-threaded by design (cardinal
#     rule: no real threads in sim) and tests legitimately use getenv for
#     seed/size knobs. The forbidden-lint already guards rand/threads in
#     non-provider code.
#   - branch-clone / misplaced-widening-cast / switch-missing-default-case are
#     DISABLED: each fires on deliberate systems-code (distinct fault/op/buggify
#     branches that share a value but document distinct intent; intentional
#     digit-parse widening casts and printf arg casts; exhaustive index/enum
#     switches with no default). All non-bugs, all reviewed — they bury the
#     real signal (clang-analyzer + the load-bearing bugprone patterns below).
Checks: >
  -*,
  clang-analyzer-*,
  bugprone-*,
  concurrency-*,
  performance-*,
  cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-member-init,
  cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-static-cast-downcast,
  cppcoreguidelines-owning-memory,
  cppcoreguidelines-no-malloc,
  cppcoreguidelines-slicing,
  cppcoreguidelines-virtual-class-destructor,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -bugprone-narrowing-conversions,
  -bugprone-implicit-widening-of-multiplication-result,
  -bugprone-exception-escape,
  -bugprone-branch-clone,
  -bugprone-misplaced-widening-cast,
  -bugprone-switch-missing-default-case,
  -concurrency-mt-unsafe

WarningsAsErrors: 'clang-analyzer-*,bugprone-*,concurrency-*,cppcoreguidelines-*'
HeaderFilterRegex: '.*/(core|providers|storage|log|txn|query|harness|consensus|tests)/.*'
FormatStyle: none
